     1	# Gold Standard — Backward-Facing Step
     2	# Corroborating literature:
     3	#   - Le, Moin & Kim 1997, J. Fluid Mech. 330, 349-374 — DNS at Re_H=5100
     4	#     with expansion ratio 1.2, reports Xr/H=6.28.
     5	#   - Driver & Seegmiller 1985, AIAA J. 23(2), 163-171 — experiment at
     6	#     Re_H≈37500 fully-turbulent, reports Xr/H=6.26.
     7	#   - Armaly et al. 1983, J. Fluid Mech. 127, 473-496 — laminar→
     8	#     transitional experimental envelope.
     9	#
    10	# Anchor choice (DEC-V61-046 round-3 R2-M2, 2026-04-23):
    11	#   The whitelist runs this case at Re_H=7600 (bulk-velocity/step-height
    12	#   Reynolds number), in the post-transition regime where both literature
    13	#   anchors above (5100 DNS, 37500 experiment) bracket the plateau within
    14	#   the declared 10% tolerance. The stored reference_values[].value=6.26
    15	#   is retained for whitelist continuity — it is within 0.3% of the
    16	#   Le/Moin/Kim 6.28 and matches the Driver & Seegmiller experimental
    17	#   number exactly, which is how the harness started. It is therefore a
    18	#   BLENDED engineering anchor rather than a pure Le/Moin/Kim number.
    19	#   The comparator's 10% tolerance absorbs the 0.02 literature spread
    20	#   without papering over the real sensitivity: the post-transition
    21	#   plateau is "weakly Re-sensitive", not a tight <2% claim, and the
    22	#   remaining drift depends on expansion ratio, inlet BL state, and 2D/3D
    23	#   effects that the adapter's 2D-empty patch treatment does not model.
    24	# Expansion ratio 1.125, incompressible, steady.
    25	# INTERNAL flow over a backward-facing step.
