     1	schema_version: 2
     2	case_id: turbulent_flat_plate
     3	source: "Blasius 1908 / Schlichting Boundary Layer Theory (7th ed.) Ch.7"
     4	literature_doi: "10.1007/978-3-662-52919-5"
     5	note: >
     6	  REGIME CORRECTION (Gate Q-new Case 4 · Path A, 2026-04-20): case_id retained
     7	  for stability but the physics is now LAMINAR Blasius, not turbulent Spalding.
     8	  Re=50000, plate_length=1.0m → Re_x=25000 at x=0.5, Re_x=50000 at x=1.0. Both
     9	  deep in laminar regime (transition ~Re_x=3e5–5e5). Blasius similarity solution:
    10	  Cf = 0.664/√Re_x. At x=0.5m: 0.00420. At x=1.0m: 0.00297.
    11	  Previous gold (0.0076 via Prandtl 1/7-power Spalding fit) was physically
    12	  incorrect — the 1/7-law is validated for turbulent BL (Re_x ≳ 5e5), not here.
    13	  See DEC-V61-006 + docs/whitelist_audit.md §5.2.
    14	physics_contract:
    15	  geometry_assumption: "Flat plate with zero-pressure-gradient external flow; x measured from leading edge; thin 2D slice (empty side patches) with a single wall-normal direction carrying the boundary layer"
    16	  reference_correlation_context: "ref_value 0.00420 at x=0.5m uses the Blasius laminar similarity solution Cf=0.664/√Re_x evaluated at Re_x=25000. Blasius is the exact self-similar solution of the Prandtl BL equations under ZPG with no-slip wall; it is exact for laminar flow at all Re_x below transition. Adapter runs simpleFoam with turbulenceProperties laminar; no wall-function model is active."
    17	  physics_precondition:
    18	    - condition: "Flow is LAMINAR at x_target (not turbulent or transitional) — Blasius similarity valid"
    19	      satisfied_by_current_adapter: true
    20	      evidence_ref: "whitelist declares turbulence_model: laminar per DEC-V61-006; adapter instantiates turbulenceProperties simulationType laminar (no k/ω/ε transport equations solved). Re_x ≤ 50000 is well below transition."
    21	    - condition: "Wall-cell gradient extraction uses interior cells (wall-cell skip), so τ_w is computed on the first-second interior-cell Δu/Δy rather than the possibly-degenerate wall-cell itself"
    22	      satisfied_by_current_adapter: true
    23	      evidence_ref: "src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6870-6879 _compute_wall_gradient — rejects if len(interior_samples)<2; uses (c0,u0)(c1,u1) for delta"
    24	    - condition: "Mesh BL resolution sufficient for laminar Blasius profile at Re_x=25000–50000 — at least 20 cells across δ_99 with wall grading"
    25	      satisfied_by_current_adapter: true
    26	      evidence_ref: ".planning/STATE.md records turbulent_flat_plate mesh at 80 y-cells with 4:1 wall grading. Blasius δ_99=5·√(ν·x/U); at U=1, ν=1/50000, x=0.5: δ_99=0.0224m. 80 cells over H=1.0 with 4:1 grading → ~50 cells within y<0.0224, well-resolved."
    27	    - condition: "Spalding-fallback branch is INACTIVE under laminar contract — extraction must be clean, no formula substitution"
    28	      satisfied_by_current_adapter: partial
    29	      evidence_ref: "src/foam_agent_adapter.py Spalding-fallback is still present in code (line ~6924). Under laminar BL and mesh-resolved extraction the measured Cf should be <0.01 organically, never triggering fallback. If fallback does fire it now indicates a genuine extraction failure (not a regime mismatch). Follow-up audit: add an assertion that extractor fallback did NOT fire when contract is laminar."
    30	  contract_status: "SATISFIED_UNDER_LAMINAR_CONTRACT — Blasius is the exact analytical solution for the declared physics. Residual uncertainty is numerical (mesh resolution + schemes) and should fit within the 10% tolerance. Any deviation >10% now unambiguously indicates an adapter or mesh bug, not a regime-mismatch hazard."
