     9	  geometry_assumption: "Intended: axisymmetric jet with wedge geometry, D=0.05 m nozzle, h/d=2.0, heated plate at z=z_max. Actual (adapter): 2D PLANAR slice — not a wedge. r=[0,5D], z=[-D/2, H+D/2]; axis patch declared `empty` (src/foam_agent_adapter.py:5184-5185), not `wedge`. A 2D-planar slice has fundamentally different stagnation-region dynamics than a true axisymmetric flow."
    10	  reference_correlation_context: "Cooper 1984 / Behnad et al. 2013 report Nusselt-number distribution Nu(r/d) for an axisymmetric heated impinging jet at Re=10000. Peak Nu=25 at the stagnation point comes from axisymmetric converging streamlines; a planar slice does not converge azimuthally and will under-predict the peak."
